commit.message: [version] Bump version to 1.6.3

[endedness] Fix problem on bigendians with 'capture_parameter'

On bigendian architectures a value with fewer bytes, if stored in a
value, or as in this case a union, are stored towards the upper end of
the larger value. This is in contrast to little-endians which will
store them at the lower end.

[messages] For unexpected calls, use location of current test instead of mock

When an unexpected call is catched it is of no use to point to the
mock function. Instead point to the test so that it can be inspected.

This required introducing a variable to keep the current
test (CgreenTest) which contains the locus of the test.

This fixes #268

the compilation fails, does not need it, so the `#include` can be
